Chapter 8: The Hard Reboot
The moment Ren’s palm met the console, the world didn’t explode. It stuttered.
The purple light froze. The roar of Kaelen’s flames turned into a low-bitrate buzz. Ren felt a coldness sharper than ice travel from his fingertips, up his arm, and directly into his spine. It wasn't the Void’s hunger—it was the sensation of a thousand streams of data screaming as they were forced into a bottleneck.
[Critical Error: Unauthorized Deconstruction in Progress.]
[Target: The Great Archive (Downlink Segment).]
[Warning: User 'Ren' is bypassing the Safety Partition!]
"What are you doing?!" Aris’s voice was no longer human. It was a layered, distorted screech. She tried to move toward Ren, but the purple light was now lashing out, silver sparks jumping from the console and pinning her to the platform like static-electricity harpoons.
"Ren! Get out of there!" Mira screamed from the edge of the pit.
Ren couldn't move. His hand was fused to the metal by a web of glowing silver geometry. He watched the "Download Bar" in his vision.
[Download Progress: 99.1%... 99.2%... ERROR.]
[Corruption Detected. Initializing Quarantine.]
"You... you little glitch," Aris hissed, her human skin beginning to flake away like burnt paper, revealing a frame of shimmering, violet obsidian beneath. "You think you can stop the update? You're just breaking the vessel!"
"I'm not stopping it," Ren gritted out through clenched teeth. His vision was turning into a mess of red pixels. "I'm... changing the destination."
[Skill Evolution Triggered!]
[ 'Structural Deconstruction' has reached Level Max for Current Rank.]
[New Skill Unlocked: 'Source Code Redirection' (Level 1).]
Ren felt a surge of heat. He didn't pull back; he pushed. He imagined the data of the students—Mira’s anxiety, Jax’s strength, Kaelen’s fire—and instead of letting it go up into the sky, he forced it back down. He sent it into the metal of the platform, into the very ground of Site 9.
The purple pillar turned a blinding, violent silver.
[Downlink Interrupted.]
[Data Purged from the Cloud.]
[Local Storage Initialized: User 'Ren' has been designated as the Temporary Cache.]
A shockwave of pure information slammed into Ren’s mind. He saw the history of the Gates, the true faces of the Association's Board of Directors, and the terrifying scale of the "Administrator" waiting in the dark.
Then, the pillar collapsed.
The light imploded with a sound like a dying star. The force threw Kaelen backward, his flames extinguished. Aris was blasted into the fog, her obsidian form shattering into a thousand fragments.
Ren was thrown into the dirt, the silver mark on his hand glowing so bright it was visible through his sleeve.
Silence returned to Site 9. The yellow fog began to thin, revealing a grey, morning sky.
[Quest Complete: The Traitor's Banquet.]
[Rewards: +500 Exp, +1 Mystery Key, +10 Stat Points.]
[System Status: Rebooting... 1%...]
"Ren?"
He heard boots crunching on gravel. Mira and Jax scrambled down into the pit. Kaelen followed slowly, clutching his charred arm, his eyes wide with a mix of awe and terror.
Ren lay in the dust, breathing hard. He looked at his hand. The geometric pattern had grown, now snaking up toward his wrist.
"The light... the Professor... it's all gone," Mira whispered, kneeling beside him. She looked at the console, which was now just a melted lump of slag. "Ren, your eyes. They’re... they’re glowing silver."
Ren blinked, and the HUD in his vision slowly faded. The status bars over his friends disappeared. He pushed himself up, his muscles screaming.
"The extraction," Kaelen muttered, looking at the empty sky. "It didn't happen. We’re still here."
"The extraction was a lie," Ren said, his voice raspy. He looked at Kaelen. "Are you okay?"
Kaelen looked at his own hands, then at Ren. The arrogance was completely gone. "I couldn't even scratch her. But you... you tore the whole system apart. What are you, Ren? No Zero has that kind of output."
Ren looked at the horizon. In the distance, he could hear the sound of real Association sirens—the recovery teams finally arriving now that the "interference" was gone.
"I'm the guy who broke the exam," Ren said. He felt a heavy weight in his mind—the 'Data Cache' he had stolen. He knew things now. Dangerous things.
[Notification: 1 New Message from 'The Administrator'.]
[Open?]
Ren ignored the prompt as the first Association transport broke through the fog. He had to hide it. He had to go back to the school as "The Zero," but the game had changed.
The monsters weren't just in the breaches anymore. They were the ones who had built the school.
Ren has survived the "Final Exam," but he’s now carrying a piece of the Void’s own code inside him.
